vulnerability.name: USN-5770-1
vulnerability.description: Todd Eisenberger discovered that certain versions of GNU Compiler Collection (GCC) could be made to clobber the status flag of RDRAND and RDSEED with specially crafted input. This could potentially lead to less randomness in random number generation.

statements.status_notes: GNU Compiler Collection's (GCC) random number generation could be made less random with specially crafted input. Available with Ubuntu Pro.
